 These capsules will be taken for a period of 4 months.

 A battery of neuropsychological tests will be administered at baseline, after 4 months, and after an additional four months of follow-up to assess cognitive performance and motor function.

 Emotional state will be assessed with the Beck Depression Inventory at each of the three aforementioned points.

 After the follow-up period, all test results will be analyzed and compared to determine the efficacy and safety of 4-aminopyridine on the cognitive performance and motor function of patients.

 Mann-Whitney U will be used for statistical analysis.

